MPs took DCI chief Ndegwa Muhoro to task over slow investigations into multimillion-shilling corruption scandals.He was questioned about the status of investigations into the millions stolen from the Youth Fund. Nominated MP Mutemi Mutua accused the DCI of laxity. &ldquo;When a matter takes two to three years before investigations are concluded, it has been politicised. We are frustrated that investigations are not being concluded,&rdquo; he said.Igembe North MP Joseph M&rsquo;eruaki, who chaired the session, said the matter is serious. He said both the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission and judiciary have said they are frustrated when addressing cases.Muhoro said, &ldquo;We are not where we want to be, but we have to appreciate we have made significant progress.&rdquo;